# Browser UI

Browser clients live under `static/` (JSX/JS sources) and `frontend/` (esbuild pipeline). Bundles commit to `static/dist/`.

## Build

```bash
make static-js      # npm ci + esbuild → static/dist/*.js
make build          # includes static-js unless SKIP_STATIC_JS=1
```

Regenerate bundles after editing `static/mail/`, `static/admin/`, `static/auth/`, or `frontend/`. CI verifies `static/dist/` matches sources.

## Architecture

| Layer | Location |
|-------|----------|
| Mail app shell | `static/mail/mail-app.jsx`, `static/mail/index.html` |
| Compose (PGP + protected link) | `static/mail/compose.jsx` |
| Client-side filters | `static/mail/mail-filter-engine.js`, `static/mail/mail-filter-ledger.js` |
| Local body search | `static/mail/search/` (IndexedDB worker per ADR 0008) |
| Settings | `static/mail/mail-settings.jsx` |
| Admin embed | `static/admin/` → lazy `static/dist/mail-admin-embed.js` |
| Auth (SRP, keygen) | `static/auth/` |
| Shared components | `static/shared/` |
| Protected link viewer | `static/protected/` |

## Security controls

These apply regardless of React vs vanilla:

| Control | Where |
|---------|-------|
| Server authorization | `internal/httpserver/` — handlers must not trust client-only flags |
| CSP / page headers | `internal/httpserver/secure_page_headers.go`; tests in `secure_surfaces_test.go` |
| MIME / HTML safety | Mail read/compose — no raw HTML from untrusted mail without sandbox + sanitizer |
| Dependency pinning | `frontend/package.json`; refresh SRI on vendor bumps |

## Key unlock flow

The unlock modal (`static/mail/unlock-modal.jsx`) handles all key states:
1. Ordinary unlock — derive KEK, unwrap account key
2. Missing account — generate account + identity, bootstrap via API
3. Missing identity — mint default identity for user's email

Key order is always **account first, identity second** so identity privkeys can be PGP-wrapped to the account pubkey.

## Normative sources for mobile parity

When mobile implements a feature, these browser files are the spec:

- Compose: `static/mail/compose.jsx`
- Reply drafts: `buildReplyComposeDraft` in `static/mail/mail-app.jsx`
- Filters: `static/mail/mail-filter-engine.js`
- Settings: `static/mail/mail-settings.jsx` (`SETTINGS_SECTIONS`)

## Migration target (ADR 0012)

The recorded migration order is: **auth → thin TS → admin shell → mail last**. Target stack is templ + vanilla JS + TypeScript, moving away from React where practical. New features may use either approach; large refactors should move toward the target.

## Do not

- Use `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` on untrusted mail content without sanitizer
- Import React from CDN — use vendored builds in `static/vendor/`
- Skip `make static-js` before committing UI changes
- Add new browser capabilities without updating [client-parity-roadmap.md](docs/client-parity-roadmap.md)
- Add new API routes that expose plaintext mail body search (ADR 0008)
